data.title: Barcelona 1992, winner's medal, gold, awarded to Bernd DITTERT (GDR) for cycling, team time trial.
data.meta_description: The medal is openwork at its top to insert the ribbon. Medal with ribbon in Olympic colors. Obverse: medallion with representation of a woman, allegory of Glory, holding a laurel wreath in her right hand and a palm branch in her left hand. She is seated at the level of a horizontal frieze. To her left and under her are laurel branches. Caption: "XXV / OLIMPIADA / BARCELONA / 1992". Olympic symbol under the caption. To the left of the allegory, above the frieze, we find the manufacturer's mark (an M surmounted by a crown) as well as the engraver's initials "XC". Reverse: emblem of the Games.
data.text:
Physical description

The medal is openwork at its top to insert the ribbon. Medal with ribbon in Olympic colors. Obverse: medallion with representation of a woman, allegory of Glory, holding a laurel wreath in her right hand and a palm branch in her left hand. She is seated at the level of a horizontal frieze. To her left and under her are laurel branches. Caption: "XXV / OLIMPIADA / BARCELONA / 1992". Olympic symbol under the caption. To the left of the allegory, above the frieze, we find the manufacturer's mark (an M surmounted by a crown) as well as the engraver's initials "XC". Reverse: emblem of the Games.
